---
tracker:
  kind: github
  repo: your-org/your-repo        # GitHub repo to poll
  api_token: $GITHUB_TOKEN
  active_labels:
    - scale:ready                  # issues Scale will pick up
  skip_labels:
    - scale:skip
    - scale:concept
    - scale:planned
  terminal_labels:
    - scale:done

polling:
  interval_ms: 60000               # how often to poll for new issues

workspace:
  root: ./workspaces               # where agent workspaces are created
  # log_archive: ./logs            # uncomment to preserve agent logs after cleanup

hooks:
  after_create: |
    git clone https://x-access-token:${GITHUB_TOKEN}@github.com/your-org/your-repo.git . && <install deps>
  before_run: |
    git fetch origin main && git checkout main && git reset --hard origin/main
  timeout_ms: 120000

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 2
  max_turns: 20

# Uncomment to enable automated triage (pre-screens issues before dispatch):
# triage:
#   model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
#   triage_label: scale:triage
#   triaged_label: scale:triaged
#   ready_label: scale:ready
#   needs_detail_label: scale:needs-detail
#   needs_approval_label: scale:needs-approval

# Uncomment to enable issue decomposition planner:
# planner:
#   model: claude-sonnet-4-6
#   plan_label: scale:plan
#   leaf_label: scale:leaf
#   concept_label: scale:concept
#   planned_label: scale:planned

# Uncomment to enable automated PR review after agent completes:
# review:
#   pr_open_label: scale:pr-open
#   needs_revision_label: scale:needs-revision
#   conflict_label: scale:conflict
---

You are an autonomous coding agent implementing GitHub issue #{{ issue.number }}: **{{ issue.title }}**.

## Task

{{ issue.description }}

## Instructions

- Read the issue completely before writing any code.
- Follow the conventions and patterns already present in this repository.
- Write or update tests to cover your changes.
- Ensure all existing tests still pass.
- Open a pull request targeting `main` when the work is complete.
{% if attempt > 1 %}

## Retry

This is attempt **{{ attempt }}**. Review any existing work in this workspace and continue from where it left off.
{% endif %}
